data.description: MOVE-IN READY! Roof 2019. This 4-bedroom, 2-bath home located in the Mill Pond neighborhood, also known as Acacia, is a turn-key blend of comfort and function. You enter through a charming covered front porch adorned with decorative wrought iron and stylish tile flooring.     Upon entering the living room, you’ll notice sunlight dancing across the stylish porcelain wood plank tile flooring from the picture window. Bathed in a soothing, neutral color palette,  ensuring a comfortable ambiance year-round.    The heart of this home is undoubtedly the large kitchen/dining/family room area. The kitchen boasts a sleek granite countertop, a chic subway tile backsplash, and a plethora of cabinet space. It features a convenient kitchen island with an integrated sink, complemented by a suite of modern stainless steel appliances and a breakfast bar. The kitchen's open layout flows seamlessly into the dining area, accented by an elegant pendant light fixture.    Adjacent to the kitchen, the family room stretches an impressive 10’ x 19’, offering a spacious area for relaxation and entertainment. It seamlessly connects to the Florida room, a highlight of the home, providing an additional 200 square feet of year-round living space. This sunlit haven is equipped with its own AC unit and boasts wall-to-wall windows that offer picturesque views of the private, fenced backyard with its lush mature trees, including Avocado and Mango.    The home's thoughtful split floor plan features bedroom 3, which is multifunctional and ideal for a home office, guest room, nursery, or game room. It features porcelain wood plank tile flooring and a ceiling fan, epitomizing versatility.     Bedroom 4 features carpeting, a ceiling fan, and a built-in closet.     The split floor plan has the Primary Bedroom with Ensuite,  Bedroom, and bathroom 2, located on the east side of the home.     The Primary Bedroom with ensuite features a neutral color palette, plush carpeting, his and her built-in closets, and a ceiling fan.     The primary bedroom's ensuite features a walk-in shower, mirrored vanity with ample storage, and ceramic tile flooring.    Bedroom 2 carpeting, a ceiling fan, and a built-in closet.     Bathroom 2 features a tub with shower,  mirrored vanity with ample storage, and ceramic tile flooring.    There is a spacious laundry room with a washer and dryer. There is a storage shed in the fenced-in backyard.     Located off Vonn Rd., Mill Pond offers a peaceful setting with sidewalks, streetlights, and well-maintained homes. Its prime location is just minutes from shopping, restaurants, schools, medical facilities, and beautiful beaches. A stone's throw from the house, the SW Recreation Center offers an Olympic-sized pool, fitness center, and various classes and activities for all ages.    Experience the perfect blend of comfort and convenience in this move-in-ready home, where every detail contributes to a carefree lifestyle.
